citeinfo.title: Rivers, 1 to 1,000,000

descript.abstract:
The Alaska Department of Natural Resources (ADNR) has combined rivers for several Digital Chart of the World (DCW) tiles into one coverage. Some edits were made where arcs were missing (Taku River, near Juneau). The coverage was clipped to the State of Alaska boundary. The islands and river polygons were reselected out of the coverage for simplification.
The river data were combined from the DNNET coverages comprising the following 5 degree by 5 degree tiles for Alaska:
AK 12,22,23,32,33 AL 21,31,32 BK 12,13,22,23,33 BL 11,12,13,21,22,23,31,32,33 CK 12,23,33 CL 11,12,13,21,22,23,31 DK 12,13,22,23 ZK 22,32

descript.supplinf:
Procedures_Used: This coverage was taken from ESRI's Digital Chart of the World. It is clipped to the State of Alaska. This data was extracted from the DNNET coverage for each tile that covers Alaska. For more info see - DCW Data Dictionary
Revisions: 02/25/98 - D. Mortenson Renamed from dcw_rivers or $DCW_RIVERS to rvr1mil.
01/10/97 - M. Gorham Performed a clean on cover.
12/18/96 - D. Mortenson Taku River (near Juneau) was missing some of its arcs. Added some arcs to fill in where it should be.
Notes: Date Received: 8/93 Verified: E. Kenning Documented by: E. Kenning 6/94 To use the ARCs for this coverage: ---------------------------------- UNSEL $DCW_RIVERS line dnlntype = 99 (this will remove all connectors between rivers-lakes and oceans)
To use the POLYs for this coverage: ----------------------------------- RESEL $DCW_RIVERS poly type = R (this will select all the RIVER polys)
UNSEL $DCW_RIVERS poly type = I (this will unselect all the ISLAND polys)

DNLNTYPE DESCRIPTION -------- ----------- 1 Streams, rivers, channelized rivers 2 Inland shorelines 8 Connectors (used to separate inland water from open ocean or ocean ice. It is derived from the border between the shade for inland water - dark blue, and open ocean or ocean ice - light blue - on the ONC sheets. 99 None
DNLNSTAT DESCRIPTION -------- ----------- 1 Perennial (used for streams only) 2 Non-perennial (used for streams only) 3 Definite (used for inland shorelines only) 88 ONC module boundary 99 None - no status attribute associated w/ feature.
